<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

Transforms TiddlyWiki into an app platform. Define full-viewport applications with named grid layouts, statewrap-powered state channels, and view tiddlers bound to layout slots. A floating action button lets you switch between apps and the default wiki at any time.

!! Features

* Full-viewport app layouts using CSS grid with predefined templates (5 built-in)
* Each app gets its own statewrap channels, defaults, and reactive rules
* View slots transclude tiddlers that communicate via statewrap channels
* Always-visible floating action button for app switching
* Edit mode modals: channel editor, rule editor, debug inspector with layout switcher
* Layout switching with automatic config persistence (view bindings, splits, proportions)
* Extensible: register apps by tagging tiddlers, add custom layout templates

!! Prerequisites

* TiddlyWiki 5.3.0 or later
* statewrap plugin

!! Quick start

# Add `rimir/appify` to `tiddlywiki.info` plugins
# Restart server
# Click the floating grid button (bottom-right) to see the demo "Project Manager" app
# To create your own app: tag a tiddler with `$:/tags/rimir/appify/app` and set the `appify-*` fields

